Commentary Text: Thakur to Rahul, out Caught by Lalit Yadav!! Lalit Yadav, after dropping one a couple of overs back, has taken a brilliant one this time! This has been hit hard and flat, it's going over Yadav's head at the cover boundary. And he doesn't have much leeway either as he's quite close to the ropes. But Yadav jumps, grabs it over his head, and lands inside the boundary. A slower ball outside off, it's in the shorter side, and Rahul times it superbly. But he's been undone by Yadav. A superb innings comes to an end. Rahul c Lalit Yadav b Thakur 77(51) [4s-4 6s-5]

Commentary Text: Mohsin Khan to Pant, out Bowled!! Lazy! There is a lot of laziness in Pant's strokeplay quite often. This is a simple length delivery that could have been nudged to the on-side. That's exactly what Pant tried to do. If his childhood coach was in that dressing room right now he would make Pant run 10 rounds around the ground for not moving his feet. Never tried to cover the line of this length ball and he tried to play with his hands. Stuff that irks any coach. He was set, was timing the ball and could have easily batted through like a Buttler or a KL, but he's opened the door for LSG himself. Pant excites you with his audacity but he also does this. Pant b Mohsin Khan 44(30) [4s-7 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Gowtham to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by de Kock!! What a change, what a big wicket. Flat, fast and fullish, Marsh stayed back and had a big slash at it without moving his feet. Commentary Text: Mohsin Khan to Warner, out Caught by Ayush Badoni!! Warner stands his ground as he thinks the catch might not be clean. It's been referred upstairs. Badoni is celebrating though. Commentary Text: Chameera to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Gowtham!! There's the length to Shaw. After getting smoked down the ground having pitched it up, Chameera decides to hit the pitch hard.
